deferred payment
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:[sp. NZ use] the payment for land in instalments, 19th cent.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: .. a legal phrase. `Land on deferred payment'; `Deferred payment settler'; `Pastoral deferred payment.' These expressions in New Zealand have reference to the mode of statutory alienation of crown lands, known in other colonies as conditional sale, etc., i.e. sale on time payment, with conditions binding the settler to erect improvements, ending in his acquiring the free-simple. The system is obsolete, but many titles are still incomplete.
